<span class="header1">DESIGNING AND ENGINEERING</span>
<p>Another good way to combine your interests in nature, the arts,
and communications is to put your skills to use in design and
engineering. These occupations are very technical. To do them, you
must be good at logical thinking and planning. You must also
be able to demonstrate your plan or create a sample of the new
product you have developed. Those who enjoy careers in these fields
are very precise people. They like detailed work and are willing to
spend time ensuring that things are done right.</p>
<p>Let's look at three occupations that may interest you.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Urban Planner</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/AB/43137.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Urban Planner" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>The word "urban" means "city." An urban planner
works with agencies that are concerned with the growth of cities. As
an urban planner, you would help to see that cities grew in ways
that were good for the environment and for people.  You might decide
that a new street is needed or that old buildings should be
repaired. You might work to ensure that water and sewage are
available when new communities are developed.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Employers require at least a bachelor's degree.
You will need a master's degree to advance in this field.  You also
need to be creative and able to see the "big picture" when faced
with a complex problem.  To see if urban issues interest you,
volunteer with groups that work to make their city a better place to
live.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage for urban
planners was $74,350 in May 2019.</blockquote>

<hr size="1">

	<span class="header2">Industrial Designer</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/AB/C0777_50.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Industrial Designer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you like to create things that others want,
you may become an industrial designer.  An industrial designer plans
and makes manufactured products such as toys, cars, or exercise
equipment for others to buy. To succeed at this occupation, you need
to be artistic. You also need to understand what consumers want to
buy.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Employers require at least a bachelor's degree.
They look for experience as well. You will also need a flair for
seeing where a product can be improved or a new product is needed.
Spend time with people who "tinker," - play with products to see if
they can be improved.  Obtain part-time work in a manufacturing
setting, if possible.  Find a way to be around people who can teach
you informally how to think about products.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage for industrial designers
was $68,890 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr  size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Land Surveyor</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/AB/43169.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Land Surveyor" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you enjoy working outdoors with others, you
may become a land surveyor.  A land surveyor works with a team of
two to four people to measure land and map out property boundaries.
Construction crews cannot start building until the land has been
surveyed.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Most surveyors have a bachelor's degree. Licensure is required to offer surveying services to the public.  A part-time job with a surveying company could help
you determine if you would like to become a land surveyor.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage for land surveyors was
$63,420 in May 2019. </blockquote>

